    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="• two municipalities have a very high global acute malnutrition (GAM) prevalence (&gt;15%): Barsalogho IDP site (16.1 per cent GAM and 4.3 per cent SAM) Centre-Nord region, Gorom-Gorom (18.4 per cent Global Acute Malnutrition (MAG) and 6 per cent Severe Acute Malnutrition (SAM), Sahel region • four municipalities have a high GAM rate (between 10 per cent and 15 per cent) • five municipalities have a moderate prevalence of GAM (&lt;10%) • children aged 6-23 months are more vulnerable to GAM than children 24-59 months, as the rates are higher in that age group • infant mortality rates in all communes and on the site are below the emergency threshold of 2 per cent. However, the results show that the situation is worry some in Barsalogho (1.3 per cent) and in the municipality of Gorgadji (1.7 per cent), where mortality rates have reached 1 per cent. [from a nutrition survey conducted in 11 municipalities in the Centre Nord, Nord, Sahel, and Est regions]"/>
